In his manly fashion he wants to be short and brief,

16
00:01:09.960 --> 00:01:11.560
I sometimes go on.

17
00:01:11.600 --> 00:01:16.240
So these are little things but they are very entertaining also.

18
00:01:16.280 --> 00:01:18.800
For instance, lately I have to tell him,

19
00:01:18.800 --> 00:01:23.760
I'm so grateful because how we complement each other.

20
00:01:23.800 --> 00:01:26.240
For instance, in the beginning I didn't know this.

21
00:01:26.280 --> 00:01:27.520
In the beginning I thought,

22
00:01:27.560 --> 00:01:33.440
oh, Alan is also calm and detached and nothing can move him.

23
00:01:33.480 --> 00:01:39.960
Whereas I was more bubbly and I had a bit more temperamental perhaps.

24
00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:42.880
Yeah, so there.

25
00:01:42.880 --> 00:01:46.800
Now I think, thank God I have him like a soundboard

26
00:01:46.840 --> 00:01:52.440
to witness my things and then we all come down again nicely.

27
00:01:52.480 --> 00:01:55.360
This is just an example that I, over the years,

28
00:01:55.400 --> 00:01:57.120
I didn't see this at the beginning.

29
00:01:57.160 --> 00:02:02.720
I thought, my goodness, he's such a yogi but he's not so emotional.

30
00:02:02.760 --> 00:02:08.640
He's so, whereas I am, so now I know for sure this is very, very good

31
00:02:08.680 --> 00:02:11.800
for both of us to balance each other and we enjoy this

32
00:02:11.800 --> 00:02:14.600
and find it quite humorous most of the time.

33
00:02:14.640 --> 00:02:17.040
So...

34
00:02:17.080 --> 00:02:19.440
And which year was that?

35
00:02:19.480 --> 00:02:21.680
Which year did you get married?

36
00:02:21.720 --> 00:02:24.040
All right, so we got married in 1987.

37
00:02:24.080 --> 00:02:27.120
Let's go back to that point.

38
00:02:27.160 --> 00:02:30.720
Why it happened, I have to say at that time,

39
00:02:30.760 --> 00:02:34.400
it was quite a different situation for me.

40
00:02:34.400 --> 00:02:39.040
In 1987, I was...

41
00:02:39.080 --> 00:02:44.560
No, that was 87, 86, I was still married.

42
00:02:44.600 --> 00:02:46.240
That was my first...

43
00:02:46.280 --> 00:02:47.280
To someone else.

44
00:02:47.320 --> 00:02:49.040
Of course, to someone else.

45
00:02:49.080 --> 00:02:51.120
I said, what do you think?

46
00:02:51.160 --> 00:02:54.080
It was a Sahaj marriage.

47
00:02:54.120 --> 00:02:56.680
I wasn't involved.

48
00:02:56.720 --> 00:02:59.320
Shimata never asked me anything.

49
00:02:59.360 --> 00:03:03.200
It was organized by others.

50
00:03:03.200 --> 00:03:04.200
Then when Shimata...

51
00:03:04.240 --> 00:03:07.600
And also I had a small child.

52
00:03:07.640 --> 00:03:13.440
So in 86, and that small child was at that time about a year old.

53
00:03:13.480 --> 00:03:17.680
So in 1986, Shimataji came to Vienna.

54
00:03:17.720 --> 00:03:20.000
She called me to her room.

55
00:03:20.040 --> 00:03:21.920
I had no idea what to expect.

56
00:03:21.960 --> 00:03:24.400
There were other Sahaja yogis in the room.

57
00:03:24.440 --> 00:03:28.680
She asked me a few questions about that first marriage.

58
00:03:28.680 --> 00:03:30.560
And then she said to me,

59
00:03:30.600 --> 00:03:33.960
you know, I think it's better to divorce.

60
00:03:34.000 --> 00:03:37.120
And that took me completely by surprise.

61
00:03:37.160 --> 00:03:40.840
I had never asked for that.

62
00:03:40.880 --> 00:03:44.160
I had never talked to anyone about this first marriage,

63
00:03:44.200 --> 00:03:46.320
except to one person.

64
00:03:46.360 --> 00:03:49.480
Because I don't want to go into details now,

65
00:03:49.520 --> 00:03:51.160
but that's what happened.

66
00:03:51.200 --> 00:03:55.400
So Shimataji helped me there in front of witnesses.

67
00:03:55.440 --> 00:03:57.400
She dissolved that first marriage.

68
00:03:57.480 --> 00:04:00.000
And I did not ask for it.

69
00:04:00.040 --> 00:04:02.280
I was completely surprised.

70
00:04:02.320 --> 00:04:05.400
But inside of me, I knew it was the right thing.

71
00:04:05.440 --> 00:04:07.360
And at the same...

72
00:04:07.400 --> 00:04:11.720
Her same state, a day later, a day later,

73
00:04:11.760 --> 00:04:19.160
she looked at me and gave me direct advice.

74
00:04:19.200 --> 00:04:21.520
Well, she didn't say what she said.

75
00:04:21.560 --> 00:04:26.200
Okay, she said, you know, there are many good Sahaja yogis,

76
00:04:26.200 --> 00:04:28.920
many good husbands in Sahaja yoga.

77
00:04:28.960 --> 00:04:33.320
And that... Okay, why does she say that?

78
00:04:33.360 --> 00:04:37.000
And she said it twice, directly in my face.

79
00:04:37.040 --> 00:04:38.440
And that really startled me,

80
00:04:38.480 --> 00:04:39.480
because I've never...

81
00:04:39.520 --> 00:04:42.440
This was all very overwhelming for me, this procedure.

82
00:04:42.480 --> 00:04:45.520
I didn't have time to think.

83
00:04:45.560 --> 00:04:49.440
But I had been the help of brothers and sisters

84
00:04:49.480 --> 00:04:53.240
who gently coaxed me to put my name on the marriage list again,

85
00:04:53.240 --> 00:04:57.800
which I've never done, never without all these experiences.

86
00:04:57.840 --> 00:05:01.760
So I said, okay, well...

87
00:05:01.800 --> 00:05:04.440
But of course, now I had a child.

88
00:05:04.480 --> 00:05:07.600
And so just...

89
00:05:07.640 --> 00:05:09.000
Just...

90
00:05:10.880 --> 00:05:14.440
I did get put my name on the marriage list.

91
00:05:14.480 --> 00:05:17.280
Yes, then I got divorced.

92
00:05:17.320 --> 00:05:23.000
So in India then, Shimataji matched me to Alan.

93
00:05:23.320 --> 00:05:27.600
And there I was, I didn't talk to her.

94
00:05:27.640 --> 00:05:31.240
She didn't talk to me in India personally at all.

95
00:05:34.880 --> 00:05:38.920
And when I came, of course, I have different backgrounds

96
00:05:38.960 --> 00:05:46.360
than many other yogis who went there for the first time to get married.

97
00:05:46.400 --> 00:05:50.360
So in my heart was just, if it is meant to be,

98
00:05:50.360 --> 00:05:56.680
please, this Sahaja Yogi who will be solid and who will be kind to my daughter

99
00:05:56.720 --> 00:06:00.560
and who will accept her unreservedly.

100
00:06:00.600 --> 00:06:02.720
That was my wish.

101
00:06:02.760 --> 00:06:05.840
From then on, we can manage.

102
00:06:05.880 --> 00:06:08.600
And so I got introduced to Alan.

103
00:06:08.640 --> 00:06:10.520
I'm sure, brothers, I can't remember.

104
00:06:10.560 --> 00:06:12.080
It was a bit exciting.

105
00:06:12.120 --> 00:06:14.520
Someone put us in front of each other.

106
00:06:14.560 --> 00:06:15.640
Edward Socks did.

107
00:06:15.680 --> 00:06:17.360
Oh, it was Edward Socks.

108
00:06:17.400 --> 00:06:19.120
He was very excited.

109
00:06:19.440 --> 00:06:21.600
Very excited.

110
00:06:21.640 --> 00:06:28.560
So again, I looked at him and I said, well, I didn't feel anything different.

111
00:06:28.600 --> 00:06:32.080
I can't say it when I saw Alan for the first time.

112
00:06:32.120 --> 00:06:33.280
It was, uh-huh, OK.

113
00:06:33.320 --> 00:06:39.000
Like there was nothing deeply exploding in myself.

114
00:06:39.040 --> 00:06:43.480
But we got a little time to talk and I wanted to feel him out,

115
00:06:43.520 --> 00:06:47.160
how he felt about sucking on my daughter.

116
00:06:47.160 --> 00:06:53.800
And that really reassured me that he was very fine, very good, very nice.

117
00:06:53.840 --> 00:06:55.760
So I said, wow.

118
00:06:55.800 --> 00:07:00.760
So that convinced me on a level that, well, this is a husband I want

119
00:07:00.800 --> 00:07:04.400
because he accepts my daughter.

120
00:07:04.440 --> 00:07:06.200
And who was that?

121
00:07:06.240 --> 00:07:08.200
And I felt he was honest there.

122
00:07:09.760 --> 00:07:13.000
And so we took it from there.

123
00:07:13.040 --> 00:07:16.480
I tell you, it was such an intense time.

124
00:07:16.840 --> 00:07:21.360
All these things happening that I can't really remember many details.

125
00:07:21.400 --> 00:07:26.480
They would come back to me, of course, how we had to treat each other at the ceremony,

126
00:07:26.520 --> 00:07:29.920
how we had to write poetry about each other.

127
00:07:29.960 --> 00:07:32.920
I was told we were the greatest poets.

128
00:07:32.960 --> 00:07:41.120
But anyway, so in general, in a nutshell, for me, it was just the beginning

129
00:07:41.160 --> 00:07:46.040
of an evolving, very beautiful story.

130
00:07:46.640 --> 00:07:49.960
And that I now every day appreciate more.

131
00:07:50.000 --> 00:07:52.680
And I don't know why things happen the way they did.

132
00:07:52.720 --> 00:07:54.160
I have no idea.

133
00:07:54.200 --> 00:07:57.800
At least it's all in traumatically loving hearts.

134
00:07:57.840 --> 00:07:59.880
I don't need to know everything.

135
00:07:59.920 --> 00:08:01.600
But now it's good.

136
00:08:01.640 --> 00:08:05.560
And the main thing, we have two more children.

137
00:08:05.600 --> 00:08:07.960
They have been inside, they have been brought up.

138
00:08:08.000 --> 00:08:13.840
They now take hiatus and they are not currently involved,

139
00:08:13.840 --> 00:08:15.600
and involved in Sahaja Yoga.

140
00:08:15.640 --> 00:08:18.640
They respect all the Sahaja Yogis.

141
00:08:20.080 --> 00:08:23.520
And I hope it will go on many, many years.

142
00:08:23.560 --> 00:08:27.560
That's the main thing.

143
00:08:32.280 --> 00:08:33.280
Nice.

144
00:08:36.080 --> 00:08:37.240
Yeah. Okay.

145
00:08:37.240 --> 00:08:38.680
Well, a little background.

146
00:08:38.720 --> 00:08:43.960
I came to Sahaja Yoga in the fall of 1985.

147
00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:45.000
I'm sorry.

148
00:08:46.800 --> 00:08:47.800
Pardon me?

149
00:08:47.840 --> 00:08:48.840
No?

150
00:08:48.880 --> 00:08:49.880
Okay.

151
00:08:49.920 --> 00:08:53.160
I came in the fall of 1985.

152
00:08:53.200 --> 00:08:56.200
I was in Sahaja Yoga for about three months.

153
00:08:56.240 --> 00:08:59.880
Then I moved into the ashram in January.

154
00:08:59.920 --> 00:09:05.320
And then the following year in December, I left for the India tour.

155
00:09:05.320 --> 00:09:13.960
So I was actually the only Canadian that was on the whole tour there at the time.

156
00:09:14.000 --> 00:09:25.320
So I felt I found the tour to be interesting because I didn't know what to expect.

157
00:09:25.360 --> 00:09:26.520
Everything was new.

158
00:09:26.560 --> 00:09:27.560
Everything was fresh.

159
00:09:27.600 --> 00:09:31.120
Of course, there were times when the vibrations were wonderful.

160
00:09:31.160 --> 00:09:34.000
And there were times when it was more difficult.

161
00:09:34.000 --> 00:09:35.000
People were tough.

162
00:09:35.040 --> 00:09:36.160
You'd get sick, you'd yell.

163
00:09:36.200 --> 00:09:40.800
And then, of course, I had my name on the marriage list.

164
00:09:40.840 --> 00:09:44.600
I remember the leader at that time said, maybe I want to wait another year.

165
00:09:44.640 --> 00:09:48.080
And I said, no, I want my name on the list this year.

166
00:09:48.120 --> 00:09:51.120
I went there and we got matched.

167
00:09:51.160 --> 00:09:55.120
And as Edward Sogstead introduced us together.

168
00:09:55.160 --> 00:10:01.760
And I guess like a lot of people from the West, I had my own fair share of conditioning.

169
00:10:01.760 --> 00:10:05.240
And I mean, expectations.

170
00:10:05.280 --> 00:10:13.680
It's one thing to say that you are detached and you will accept whoever Shri Mataji marries you to.

171
00:10:13.720 --> 00:10:17.240
It's another thing to deal with the reality.

172
00:10:17.280 --> 00:10:27.440
So like Inga said, when I first saw her, I didn't feel one way or the other, whether this person or not that I should marry.

173
00:10:27.480 --> 00:10:30.880
I just sort of took a wait and see.

174
00:10:31.040 --> 00:10:36.520
But I do remember distinctly that I was quite happy about the fact that she had a child.

175
00:10:36.560 --> 00:10:44.160
So, yeah, I mean, I've always really liked all children for that matter.

176
00:10:44.200 --> 00:10:45.000
I like that.

177
00:10:45.040 --> 00:10:51.520
But especially little girls, because I knew that my family, the dominant tendency was just for boys as well.

178
00:10:51.560 --> 00:10:54.400
So I thought, okay, to get a little girl, that's nice.

179
00:10:54.400 --> 00:11:01.760
And the idea or concept that it's someone else's child never took hold of me.

180
00:11:01.800 --> 00:11:05.640
For some reason, I felt, okay, yeah, they're all God's children.

181
00:11:05.680 --> 00:11:10.720
And it doesn't matter who biologically they came from.

182
00:11:10.760 --> 00:11:18.960
The main thing about children is you just love them and you experience the love they have to give.

183
00:11:19.000 --> 00:11:21.520
So we went along.

184
00:11:21.520 --> 00:11:25.120
I had my up periods and I had my down periods.

185
00:11:25.160 --> 00:11:38.240
But much like Inga was saying in retrospect, you see clearly all the reasons Srimadaji had for putting me together.

186
00:11:38.280 --> 00:11:43.640
And I am very thankful to Srimadaji for matching me with Inga,

187
00:11:43.640 --> 00:11:54.120
because my one main concern was having a strong ill-being by my side in my life.

188
00:11:54.160 --> 00:11:57.360
And this is the one thing she's always been.

189
00:11:57.400 --> 00:12:00.440
She's been a real rock there.

190
00:12:00.480 --> 00:12:05.800
She had more experience in sahaja matters than I did.

191
00:12:05.800 --> 00:12:19.640
And I think that she has such strong positive qualities that I can really see helped me to balance and offset my imbalances as well.

192
00:12:19.680 --> 00:12:22.040
So that we're very happy.

193
00:12:22.080 --> 00:12:30.840
And I mean, other than that, we had a very traditional marriage that at least for sahaja at that time, we got a khatikule.

194
00:12:30.840 --> 00:12:38.360
And we rode on the grooms all rode on bullock carts in before.

195
00:12:38.400 --> 00:12:39.280
So do a cart.

196
00:12:39.320 --> 00:12:45.200
And we had the sheets of the fire and all the rest of the vibrations were, of course, wonderful.

197
00:12:45.240 --> 00:12:51.160
Whenever I put my attention on the vibrations, they were very good for us to be as a match.

198
00:12:51.200 --> 00:12:53.160
So I thought, OK.

199
00:12:53.160 --> 00:13:02.520
And then I remember very distinctly, Sharmataji talking before the marriages actually took place.

200
00:13:02.560 --> 00:13:08.160
And there was all of us that were matched and some people refused the match.

201
00:13:08.200 --> 00:13:13.080
I remember somewhere around two or three women declined.

202
00:13:13.120 --> 00:13:22.640
And boy, oh boy, I was really glad I accepted because Sharmataji really gave it to them left and right.

203
00:13:22.640 --> 00:13:28.520
And I know the other thing, of course, I had some doubts and I know I'm not the only groom like that.

204
00:13:28.560 --> 00:13:35.960
I've seen men faint when they were announced their marriage is as far as that goes.

205
00:13:36.000 --> 00:13:44.280
Because it is, you know, you just face all this stuff in yourself and it has very little to do with the person.

206
00:13:44.320 --> 00:13:47.280
It's just facing your own stuff.

207
00:13:47.480 --> 00:13:55.280
But I also remember very distinctly that I had some very powerful, rocky brothers,

208
00:13:55.320 --> 00:14:00.480
people like Greg Warr and leaders, this country and that country and so ever.

209
00:14:00.520 --> 00:14:03.240
And they're all coming up to me, yeah, congratulations.

210
00:14:03.280 --> 00:14:05.280
This will be a very good match.

211
00:14:05.320 --> 00:14:15.000
And, you know, I felt like it would be nice to discuss things in general without having people just telling me this, this, this, encouraging.

212
00:14:15.000 --> 00:14:23.160
But all said and done, like I say, Felicity mentioned it, that you see a lot of the reasons inside.

213
00:14:23.200 --> 00:14:26.400
And it's the inside things that really count.

214
00:14:26.440 --> 00:14:35.240
It's mainly, is this person a good yogini and is it someone that will love you and look after you and vice versa?

215
00:14:35.280 --> 00:14:38.920
And someone that's a good mother for your children?

216
00:14:38.920 --> 00:14:51.480
All of these qualities that are not found in today's society very much that you see in the gift that Sharmaji gave you.

217
00:14:51.520 --> 00:14:53.800
So, yeah.

218
00:14:53.840 --> 00:14:58.080
And then, oh, we got married again.

219
00:14:58.120 --> 00:15:00.120
We had a second marriage.

220
00:15:00.160 --> 00:15:03.480
I believe it, I don't know if it's called an Aryan Samaj.

221
00:15:03.480 --> 00:15:21.480
But we were married legally in a Hindu ceremony that was arranged, which was, yeah, a bit strange, you know, because that would give us the legal paperwork that we needed in order to have Inga come to America.

222
00:15:21.520 --> 00:15:24.800
So a lot of, I don't know if they've done that very many times.

223
00:15:24.840 --> 00:15:26.880
I haven't heard of anyone else.

224
00:15:26.920 --> 00:15:28.320
Kind of a funny little incident.

225
00:15:28.320 --> 00:15:42.560
There was a woman there who, at any rate, so yeah, we had that ceremony.

226
00:15:42.600 --> 00:15:50.240
And so we got married in January and somewhere in May, I believe Inga was able to make it.

227
00:15:50.280 --> 00:15:55.280
So it was really quick to immigrate into Canada.

228
00:15:56.240 --> 00:16:00.120
But I would not recommend any Aryan Samaj wedding.

229
00:16:00.160 --> 00:16:03.720
It was only adding complications.

230
00:16:03.760 --> 00:16:12.560
In the end, I had to be a bride to be sent to India so that they sent the certificate.

231
00:16:12.600 --> 00:16:16.320
I hope the bride was worthy to hear.

232
00:16:16.360 --> 00:16:18.600
So anyway, this is the site.

233
00:16:18.640 --> 00:16:22.080
I don't think this happens afterwards ever again.

234
00:16:22.080 --> 00:16:30.240
Oh, we had a honeymoon, which is great.

235
00:16:30.280 --> 00:16:31.200
Yeah, we did.

236
00:16:31.240 --> 00:16:32.600
That was actually nice.

237
00:16:32.640 --> 00:16:34.400
You wanted to send it on a honeymoon.

238
00:16:34.440 --> 00:16:34.960
That's true.

239
00:16:35.000 --> 00:16:37.840
In India, in the hotel.

240
00:16:37.880 --> 00:16:38.880
It was strange.

241
00:16:38.920 --> 00:16:41.920
You sit there and look at each other.

242
00:16:41.960 --> 00:16:43.600
It was interesting.

243
00:16:43.640 --> 00:16:44.960
You got room service.

244
00:16:45.000 --> 00:16:47.360
You could order whatever you want.

